1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-890.9 of Title 63, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. Each assisted living center shall establish and maintain an
5 internal quality assurance committee that meets at least quarterly.
6 The committee shall:
7 1. Monitor trends and incidents;
8 2. Monitor customer satisfaction measures;
9 3. Document quality assurance efforts and outcomes;
10 4. Recommend internal policies on resident care including, but
11 not limited to, policies on administration of medications; and
12 5. Perform such other duties or functions as directed by the
13 State Commissioner of Health through rule.
14 B. The quality assurance committee shall include at least the
15 following:
16 1. A Registered Nurse or physician if a medical problem is to
17 be monitored or investigated;
18 2. The assisted living center administrator;
19 3. A direct care staff person or a staff person who has
20 responsibility for administration of medications;
21 4. A pharmacist consultant if a medication problem is to be
22 monitored or investigated; and
23 5. A person who has an ownership stake in the assisted living
24 center, or his or her designee.
